rsymmetric models are perturbative and\nstable. Type IIA compactifications on toroidal orbifolds allow for $O(10)$\nYukawa couplings in the ultraviolet. We also discuss the possibility of\naccounting for the diphoton excess in a low string scale scenario via the decay\nof string axions.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 23 Dec 2015 20:48:24 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 25 Oct 2016 13:34:47 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-11-03"}
